time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @water{3/4%cup} and @butter{1%tbsp}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}(halved, peeled, sliced); finely mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Green Bell Pepper{1}(halved, cored, sliced) into strips. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Quarter @Lime{1}(quartered).

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced shallot and bell pepper. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Tear @Pulled Pork{10%ounce} into smaller pieces. Add to pan with veggies along with another large drizzle of oil. Season with @Salt{}, @Pepper{}, and @Fajita Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until pork is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Simmer until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

While pork simmers, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced shallot, half the cilantro, juice from half the lime, salt, and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper. Divide between bowls. Top with pork mixture, salsa, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, and @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> We like to call these "fiesta bowls" because they know just how to stir things up at dinnertime. They're guaranteed to keep the vibes lively!